column1: USER AGREEMENT:  As a condition for access to data provided by researchers of the Cedar Creek LTER
column2: I agree to abide by the following code of ethics.

column1: A. I agree to notify the Cedar Creek LTER scientists who gathered data if I would like to use those data in any publication. I acknowledge that these data were gathered by Cedar Creek scientists because they had already perceived the importance of these data for a variety of scientific and societal issues. I will provide them with formal recognition that
column3: may include co-authorship or acknowledgements on publications.

column1: B. I realize that the researchers who gathered these data may be using them for scientific analyses
column2: papers or publications that are currently planned or in preparation
column3: and that such activities have precedence over any that I might wish to prepare. In this case
column4: my preparation of any work may be delayed
column5: at the option of the Cedar Creek researchers involved

column1: C. Because it may be possible to misinterpret a data set if it is taken out of context
column2: I will seek the assistance and opinion of those Cedar Creek researchers involved in the design of a study and the collection of the data as I analyze the data. Moreover
column3: I realize that this computer data set is not complete
column4: and it may contain errors. The complete data set includes extensive written documentation
column5: which should be referenced to reduce the chance of errors in data and errors of interpretation.
